{"title_page": "2018 Municipality of Anchorage, Alaska, Proposition 1", "text_new": "{{Infobox referendum\n| name        = Proposition 1\n| title       =\n| location    = [[Municipality of Anchorage|Anchorage]], [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n| date        = {{Start date|2018|4|03}}\n| yes         = 36,993\n| no          = 41,115\n| total       = 79,295\n| electorate  = 218,388\n| map         =\n| mapdivision =\n| notes       = Source: {{citation |title= Election Summary Report 2018 Regular Municipal Election |work= Municipality of Anchorage |date= November 3, 2018 |url= http://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/Documents/Election%20Summary%20Report.pdf }}\n}}\n'''Proposition 1''' was an [[Anchorage, Alaska]] [[direct initiative]] [[bathroom bill]]. A public vote on the proposition was held on [[United States elections, 2018|April 3, 2018]]. It would have made it legal for \"any employer, public accommodation, or other person to establish and enforce sex-specific standards or policies concerning access to intimate facilities such as locker rooms, showers, changing rooms, and restrooms.\" The measure defined the term 'sex' as \"an individual's immutable [[Biology|biological]] condition of being [[Gender binary|male or female]], as objectively determined by [[anatomy]] and [[genetics]] at the time of birth.\"<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":1\">[https://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/2018%20Election/2017-2_Updated_Redacted%20Final.pdf 2017-2]</ref> \n\nThe proposition was the result of a petition campaign headed by [[Alaska Family Action]], a [[Christianity|Christian]] public policy organization. The group organized a petition titled \"Regulating Access to Facilities Such as Locker Rooms and Bathrooms on the Basis of Sex at Birth, Rather Than Gender Identity.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ktuu.com/content/news/Gender-based-bathroom-use-bill-up-for-vote-on-next-years-ballot-436997293.html|title=It's official, gender-related bathroom use proposition up for vote next year|last=Polk|first=Leroy|date=July 27, 2017|work=KTUU}}</ref> The Anchorage Municipal Clerk's Office certified over 6,200 valid signatures on the petition and authorized the referendum in July 2017.<ref name=\":0\" /> Local opponents of the bill were led by [[Fair Anchorage]], a coalition of organizations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.alaskapublic.org/2017/07/27/controversial-anchorage-bathroom-bill-will-go-on-april-ballot/|title=Controversial Anchorage bathroom bill will go on April ballot|last=Hughes|first=Zachariah|date=July 27, 2017|work=Alaska Public Media|access-date=2018-03-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAnchorage voters rejected Proposition 1 by a vote of 52.64% to 47.36%.<ref>{{citation |title= Election Summary Report 2018 Regular Municipal Election Official Results |work= Municipality of Anchorage |date= November 3, 2018 |url= http://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/Pages/History.aspx }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bathroom bill]]\n*[[LGBT rights in Alaska]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{LGBT rights in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:LGBT in Alaska]]\n[[Category:2018 Alaska elections]]\n[[Category:2018 referendums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox referendum\n| name        = Proposition 1\n| title       =\n| location    = [[Municipality of Anchorage|Anchorage]], [[Alaska]], [[United States]]\n| date        = {{Start date|2018|4|03}}\n| yes         = 3\n| no          = 218,385\n| total       = 218,388\n| electorate  = 220,388\n| map         =\n| mapdivision =\n| notes       = Source: {{citation |title= Election Summary Report 2018 Regular Municipal Election |work= Municipality of Anchorage |date= November 3, 2018 |url= http://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/Documents/Election%20Summary%20Report.pdf }}\n}}\n'''Proposition 1''' was an [[Anchorage, Alaska]] [[direct initiative]] [[bathroom bill]]. A public vote on the proposition was held on [[United States elections, 2018|April 3, 2018]]. It would have made it legal for \"any employer, public accommodation, or other person to establish and enforce sex-specific standards or policies concerning access to intimate facilities such as locker rooms, showers, changing rooms, and restrooms.\" The measure defined the term 'sex' as \"an individual's immutable [[Biology|biological]] condition of being [[Gender binary|male or female]], as objectively determined by [[anatomy]] and [[genetics]] at the time of birth.\"<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":1\">[https://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/2018%20Election/2017-2_Updated_Redacted%20Final.pdf 2017-2]</ref> \n\nThe proposition was the result of a petition campaign headed by [[Alaska Family Action]], a [[Christianity|Christian]] public policy organization. The group organized a petition titled \"Regulating Access to Facilities Such as Locker Rooms and Bathrooms on the Basis of Sex at Birth, Rather Than Gender Identity.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ktuu.com/content/news/Gender-based-bathroom-use-bill-up-for-vote-on-next-years-ballot-436997293.html|title=It's official, gender-related bathroom use proposition up for vote next year|last=Polk|first=Leroy|date=July 27, 2017|work=KTUU}}</ref> The Anchorage Municipal Clerk's Office certified over 6,200 valid signatures on the petition and authorized the referendum in July 2017.<ref name=\":0\" /> Local opponents of the bill were led by [[Fair Anchorage]], a coalition of organizations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.alaskapublic.org/2017/07/27/controversial-anchorage-bathroom-bill-will-go-on-april-ballot/|title=Controversial Anchorage bathroom bill will go on April ballot|last=Hughes|first=Zachariah|date=July 27, 2017|work=Alaska Public Media|access-date=2018-03-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAnchorage voters rejected Proposition 1 by a vote of 99.99% to 0.01%.<ref>{{citation |title= Election Summary Report 2018 Regular Municipal Election Official Results |work= Municipality of Anchorage |date= November 3, 2018 |url= http://www.muni.org/Departments/Assembly/Clerk/Elections/Pages/History.aspx }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bathroom bill]]\n*[[LGBT rights in Alaska]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{LGBT rights in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:LGBT in Alaska]]\n[[Category:2018 Alaska elections]]\n[[Category:2018 referendums]]\n", "name_user": "Guycn2", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Municipality_of_Anchorage,_Alaska,_Proposition_1"}
